
README: Examining Intrahemispheric Parietal-Motor Interconnectivity During Motor Imagery Using Dual-Coil Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation
Project Overview
This project investigates the intrahemispheric connectivity between the posterior parietal cortex (PPC; specifically the supramarginal gyrus) and primary motor cortex (M1) during motor imagery using dual-coil transcranial magnetic stimulation (TMS). A secondary aim was to determine whether a guided motor imagery script (LSRT) produces stronger PPC-M1 interactions than a standard motor imagery script.

Completed in April, 2026.

Contributors: Marlo Spence, Sarah Kraeutner, Alisha Davis

Contact information: Marlo Spence, UBC, email: marlo.a.spence@gmail.com
Sarah Kraeutner, UBC
Alisha Davis, UBC

Methodology: 

Data Collection: Participants completed motor imagery trials under three TMS conditions (M1-only test stimulus, dual-coil with 4ms ISI, dual-coil with 8ms ISI) across two motor imagery scripts (standard and LSRT). A conditioning pulse was delivered to the supramarginal gyrus of the PPC, followed by a test stimulus to M1. MEP amplitudes were recorded from the target hand muscle via EMG using CED Signal software.
Data Processing: Raw EMG signal files (.cfs, .sgrx) were exported and MEP peak-to-peak amplitudes were manually extracted and compiled into long-format CSV. Data were log-transformed prior to analysis.
Analysis: Paired t-tests were conducted comparing MEP amplitudes between the M1-only condition and each dual-coil ISI condition (4ms, 8ms) separately for each script. Effect sizes were calculated using Cohen's d with 95% confidence intervals. All analyses were conducted in R.

Repository Structure
├── data/
│   ├── data_raw/          # Raw electrophysiological files (.cfs, .sgrx) per participant
│   └── data_processed/
│       ├── MEP_long.csv   # Processed long-format MEP data used in analysis
│       └── data_dictionary    # Variable descriptions used in analysis
├── docs/
│   ├── final_draft_manuscript.Rmd   # R Markdown manuscript with embedded analysis
│   ├── final_draft_manuscript.html# Rendered manuscript
│   ├── final_draft_manuscript.pdf # Knitted pdf of manuscript
│   ├── references.bib         # Zotero-exported BibTeX references
│   └── apa.csl                # APA 7th edition citation style file
├── scripts/
│   └── test_script.R      # test script completed in class
├── renv.lock              # Package environment lockfile
└── data_reproducibility.Rproj

Data Description:

data/data_processed/MEP_long.csv contains trial-level MEP amplitude data in long format with the following columns:
ColumnDescription: participant_id (Participant identifier (p01, p02, p03, ...)), condition (TMS condition: TS (test stimulus / M1-only), 4ms, or 8ms (ISI for dual-coil)), mep_amplitude (MEP amplitude (mV) for each individual trial), script (Motor imagery script: standard or LSRT (guided)).
Raw data files (.cfs, .sgrx) are named by participant, visit, ISI, and block (e.g., 001_V1_4ms_standard_B1). Raw data are not publicly accessible due to the inclusion of potentially sensitive human participant data.

Reproducing the Analysis
This project uses renv for package management. To restore the environment:
renv::restore()
Required packages

dplyr
ggplot2
effsize

Steps:

Open data_reproducibility.Rproj in RStudio
Run renv::restore() to install required packages
Open final_draft_manuscript.Rmd and run to reproduce statistical analyses and figures (will require data that is not provided)
knit to reproduce the manuscript

Ethics and Data Availability:

Processed data (MEP_long.csv) are not publicly accessible due to the potentially sensitive nature of human participant data. Requests for data access can be directed to Marlo Spence (marlo.a.spence@gmail.com).

